    • Method Detail

      • getKeys

        java.util.Set<java.lang.String> getKeys()
        The method returns all the keys that the ConfigSource contains, as a read-only Set .
        Returns:
        all the keys that the ConfigSource contains as a read-only Set , any attempts to modify the returned Set may cause an exception. Empty set returned in case the config source is empty, the method never returns null.

      • hasKey

        boolean hasKey(java.lang.String key)
        The method queries whether the ConfigSource has the specified key .
        Parameters:
        key - the key to query, cannot be null.
        Returns:
        true if the ConfigSource has the key .
        Throws:
        InvalidParameterException - when key is null.

      • getString

        java.lang.String getString(java.lang.String key)
        The method queries the String value specified by key .
        Parameters:
        key - the key to search, cannot be null.
        Returns:
        the String value specified by key in the ConfigSource , or null if the key is not found.
        Throws:
        PreconditionCheckFailedException - when key is null.
